A shocking video of a schoolgirl being violently assaulted by a male schoolmate, at what is believed to be a KwaZulu-Natal school, has surfaced on social media
"Nang' umakoti" wrote on the social networking platform: "So many questions. How are people raising such angry children? What must that girls parents say? The silence of bystanders? Normal much?"
Phiwokuhle Nogwaza wrote: "Absolutely shattered and heartbroken by this".
The spokesperson for the Department of Basic Education in KZN, Muzi Mahlambi, was horrified at the video.
"We are incredibly disturbed at the brutality of this attack," he said.
He said investigations were underway and that once the school and the culprit had been identified, that decisive action would be taken.
"We are going to teach this boy a lesson he will never forget," he said.
The Mercury